identifiers.description: Object that maps the trial's sources ids with its identifiers.

is_primary.description: Is this record the primary source of data for its trial

last_verification_date.description: Date when the record's data was last verified by provider

recruitment_status.description: Trial's recruitment status (e.g. recruiting, unknown etc.)

source_url.description: URL of the record's source (where it was collected from)

status.description: Trial's status (e.g. ongoing, withdrawn, complete etc.)

trial_id.description: ID of the trial referenced in the record

trial_url.description: OpenTrials API URL of the trial referenced in the record

mappings.name: Returns a trial's details and related entities (e.g. `conditions`). - 404
Returns a trial's details and related entities (e.g. `conditions`). (application/json)

max_age.description: Maximum participant age (e.g. "12 Years", "1 Month", "15 Days"). If unknown, it's `undefined`. If no limit, it's "any". If not applicable, it's "N/A".

min_age.description: Minimum participant age (e.g. "12 Years", "1 Month", "15 Days"). If unknown, it's `undefined`. If no limit, it's "any". If not applicable, it's "N/A".

discrepancies.description: Discrepancies in trial's details between different sources

gender.description: Gender of the subjects of the trial

identifiers.description: Object that maps the trial's sources ids with its identifiers.

results_exemption_date.description: Date when a certification of exemption has been filed for the trial

target_sample_size.description: Target sample size for the trial

url.description: Source URL (where the trial was collected from)
